It seems D-day has finally arrived for former president Jacob Zuma. His long-awaited arms deal trial begins today in the High Court in Pietermaritzburg. As the original whistleblower, Public Works Minister Patricia de Lille is expected to be the first witness.  #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 PIETERMARITZBURG - Former president, Jacob Zuma's long-awaited Arm's deal trial will begin at the Pietermaritzburg High Court on Monday. As the original whistleblower, Public Works Minister, Patricia de Lille, is expected to be the first witness. READ: Analysis | Zuma trial begins Monday Questions around whether Zuma will have legal representations seems to have cleared up. His daughter has tweeted that the 79-year-old will be represented by Advocate Thabani Masuku. Watch the video above for more details on this story. Catch rolling coverage on this story on #DStv403